docs.abstract: The continent’s second-largest river is drying up amid the biggest drought in 70 years, upending ecosystems, trade and livelihoods.
docs.snippet: The continent’s second-largest river is drying up amid the biggest drought in 70 years, upending ecosystems, trade and livelihoods.
docs.lead_paragraph: ROSARIO, Argentina — The fisherman woke up early on a recent morning, banged on the fuel containers on his small boat to make sure he had enough for the day, and set out on the Paraná River, fishing net in hand.

headline.main: An Economic Lifeline in South America, the Paraná River, Is Shriveling
headline.print_headline: ‘Everything Is Dry’: In South America, a Vanishing Lifeline

byline.original: By Daniel Politi and Sebastián López Brach

docs.abstract: In a region where some populations have extremely limited access to vaccines, public health agencies are taking control of the means of production.
docs.snippet: In a region where some populations have extremely limited access to vaccines, public health agencies are taking control of the means of production.
docs.lead_paragraph: To help address unequal access to Covid-19 vaccines around the world — an issue that “remains the Achilles’ heel” of the pandemic fight —  the World Health Organization is starting a program to manufacture vaccines in Latin America and the Caribbean, Dr. Carissa Etienne, the director of the Pan American Health Organization, said Wednesday.

headline.main: The W.H.O. will address inequities by making vaccines in Latin America.

docs.abstract: President Nayib Bukele has promoted the cryptocurrency as a path to financial freedom, but economic experts and many Salvadorans worry the move brings great risks.
docs.snippet: President Nayib Bukele has promoted the cryptocurrency as a path to financial freedom, but economic experts and many Salvadorans worry the move brings great risks.
docs.lead_paragraph: MEXICO CITY — El Salvador on Tuesday became the first country to adopt Bitcoin as legal tender, allowing the cryptocurrency to be used in any transaction, from buying a cup of coffee to paying taxes.

headline.main: In Global First, El Salvador Adopts Bitcoin as Currency
headline.print_headline: In First, El Salvador Adopts Bitcoin as Legal Currency

docs.abstract: New research using hundreds of DNA samples showed that there are seven species of these hand-standing, stink-spraying mammals.
docs.snippet: New research using hundreds of DNA samples showed that there are seven species of these hand-standing, stink-spraying mammals.
docs.lead_paragraph: Black fur, white stripes, fanny full of foul-smelling liquid — everybody can identify the striped skunk. But did you know these malodorous mammals have a number of smaller cousins marked by a pattern of black-and-white Rorschach blots? They’re known as the spotted skunks, and they do something the stripeys can’t.

headline.main: Meet the Spotted Skunks. They’ve Been Keeping a Secret From Us.
headline.print_headline: Smelly Acrobats: This Skunk’s Next Trick Gets Much Less Applause

docs.abstract: A century after museum collectors surveyed Colombia’s avian fauna, a new generation of researchers returns to see what remains, and what has changed.
docs.snippet: A century after museum collectors surveyed Colombia’s avian fauna, a new generation of researchers returns to see what remains, and what has changed.
docs.lead_paragraph: FLORENCIA, Colombia — In June 1912, Leo Miller, a collector with the American Museum of Natural History, arrived in the Caquetá region of Colombia, where the eastern foothills of the Andes melt into the forested lowlands of the Amazon basin.

headline.main: Searching for Bird Life in a Former ‘Ocean of Forest’
headline.print_headline: Searching for Bird Life in a Former ‘Ocean of Forest’

byline.original: By Jennie Erin Smith and Federico Rios

docs.abstract: In the world’s plant gene banks, scientists studied how so many varieties of the humble capsicum worked their way onto our plates.
docs.snippet: In the world’s plant gene banks, scientists studied how so many varieties of the humble capsicum worked their way onto our plates.
docs.lead_paragraph: Peppers are cosmopolitan, a vegetable that comes in far more varieties than there are nations in the world. One day you can slice a mild orange bell pepper to dip in hummus. Another you may roast red peppers and blend them into a dip or a sauce of their own, like ajvar or romesco. Poblano peppers can add some heat to a dish, or even become a meal like chile rellenos. But watch out for those Carolina Reaper peppers.

headline.main: How Peppers Proliferated Around the Planet
headline.print_headline: Pickled or Not: Why There Are More Pecks Of Pepper Than Ever to Pick

docs.abstract: Many Cubans thought the Biden administration would move to normalize relations with Havana. But the president has been tougher than Donald Trump on the island’s government.
docs.snippet: Many Cubans thought the Biden administration would move to normalize relations with Havana. But the president has been tougher than Donald Trump on the island’s government.
docs.lead_paragraph: President Biden’s presidency raised expectations among many Cubans of a return to the Obama days, when the United States sought to bury the last vestige of the Cold War by restoring diplomatic relations with Havana and calling for an end to the embargo.

headline.main: Biden Ramps Up Pressure on Cuba, Abandoning Obama’s Approach
headline.print_headline: Biden Takes Harder Line To Influence Life in Cuba

docs.abstract: Most countries in the Americas collect no Covid-19 figures on Indigenous people, although that “data is essential to guide effective policies,” the official said.
docs.snippet: Most countries in the Americas collect no Covid-19 figures on Indigenous people, although that “data is essential to guide effective policies,” the official said.
docs.lead_paragraph: Countries across the Americas must do more to help Indigenous communities prevent and treat Covid-19 infections — and that starts with collecting far more extensive and reliable data, a leading World Health Organization official said on Wednesday.

headline.main: Indigenous people face a unique risk that is poorly understood, a W.H.O. official said.

docs.abstract: Citing new concerns about the spread of the coronavirus, the administration will continue to rely for now on a Trump-era policy.
docs.snippet: Citing new concerns about the spread of the coronavirus, the administration will continue to rely for now on a Trump-era policy.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — With the number of migrants crossing the southern border surging and the pandemic proving to be far from over, the Biden administration has decided to leave in place for now the public health rule that has allowed it to turn away hundreds of thousands of migrants, officials said.

headline.main: Biden Administration to Keep Using Public Health Rule to Turn Away Migrants
headline.print_headline: Administration to Keep Using Public Health Rule to Turn Away Migrants

docs.abstract: A star player’s glittering career finally gets the one honor it was missing: a major title with his national team.

docs.lead_paragraph: Lionel Messi finally ticked the last empty box in his glittering soccer career on Saturday night, leading Argentina past host Brazil, 1-0, in the final of the Copa América in Rio de Janeiro.
